    • Constructor Detail

      • OpenReadingFrameLocation

        public OpenReadingFrameLocation(java.lang.String orfCharacters,
                                int orfStartIndex,
                                int orfStopIndex,
                                int frameIndicator)
        Initialises the object. It is created with the properties it will have for its life time, since these will never change. When setting the length of the ORF Location, it is calculated from the character difference between the start and stop index, and adjusted depending on if the frame it is located in is forward or backwards.
        Parameters:
        orfCharacters - The characters within the ORF Location.
        orfStartIndex - The character index of the start of the ORF Location.
        orfStopIndex - The character index of the end of the ORF Location.
        frameIndicator - The frame that the ORF Location belongs to (minus 1)
